http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Auto-driver-dies-in-accident/article14011925.ece

An autorickshaw driver was killed when his three-wheeler collided with a car at Mavungal, near here, on Wednesday. The accident took place around 9.15 a.m. as the driver of the car who lost control of the vehicle hit the three-wheeler head-on while it was proceeding towards Pullur, the police said. The auto driver, Kannan, 50, who sustained multiple injuries died on the spot. The car was impounded by the police. The three-wheeler suffered extensive damage in the mishap. Kannan is survived by his wife, a son and a daughter.